  "prompt": "How can I receive data in MATLAB from my Android device using Bluetooth?",
  "response": "To receive data from an Android device using Bluetooth in MATLAB, you'll need to follow several steps:\n\n1. Hardware and Software Requirements:\n- MATLAB with Bluetooth support\n- Bluetooth-enabled computer\n- Android device with Bluetooth\n- Optional: Bluetooth dongle if your computer doesn't have built-in Bluetooth\n\n2. MATLAB Bluetooth Setup:\n```matlab\n% Check Bluetooth support\nhaveBluetooth = instrhwinfo('bluetooth')\n\n% Create Bluetooth object\nbtDevice = bluetooth('XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX', 1);\n% Replace XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX with your Android device's MAC address\n```\n\n3. Android App Development:\nCreate an Android app with Bluetooth sending capabilities:\n```java\n// Sample Java code for Bluetooth sending\nBluetoothSocket socket;\nOutputStream outputStream;\n\nvoid sendData(String data) {\n    try {\n        outputStream.write(data.getBytes());\n    } catch (IOException e) {\n        e.printStackTrace();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n4. MATLAB Data Reception:\n```matlab\n% Open Bluetooth connection\nfopen(btDevice);\n\n% Read incoming data\nwhile true\n    data = fscanf(btDevice);\n    % Process received data\n    disp(data);\nend\n\n% Close connection\nfclose(btDevice);\ndelete(btDevice);\n```\n\n5. Alternative: MATLAB Support Package\n- Install Bluetooth Support Package\n- Use `bluetooth()` and `read()` functions\n\nRecommendations:\n- Ensure proper Bluetooth pairing\n- Handle connection errors\n- Use appropriate data formats\n- Consider using JSON for structured data transmission",
